name: atrazine
notes: Systemic herbicide that is used to selectively control annual grasses and broadleaf weeds before they emerge

name: carfentrazone
notes: Contact herbicide used to control broadleaf and sedge weeds in cereals.

name: iodosulfuron
notes: control monocotyledonous and dicotyledonous weeds in cereal cultivation.

name: metsulfuron
notes: Organic compound classified as a sulfonylurea herbicide, which kills broadleaf weeds and some annual grasses. It is a systemic compound with foliar and soil activity, that inhibits cell division in shoots and roots

name: pendimethalin
notes: a selective herbicide used to control broadleaf weeds. and grassy weed species
